NHL to Divide Teams Into Four Regionally Based Conferences Next Season

-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 
2011-12-06T03:30:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-06/nhl-to-divide-teams-into-four-regionally-based-conferences-next-season.html
The  National Hockey League  will
switch to a four-conference setup based on geography from next
season following a vote by the board of governors.  Two conferences, which have yet to be named, will comprise
eight teams, with seven clubs in the other two, the NHL said in
a statement on its website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  